00:14:08,858 --> 00:14:11,983
It's good fodder for the
development of my shield.

257
00:14:12,067 --> 00:14:13,108
Please don't.

258
00:14:13,192 --> 00:14:15,358
I sense an ominous
aura in your shield.

259
00:14:15,442 --> 00:14:16,358
[NAOFUMI gasps]

260
00:14:16,442 --> 00:14:18,067
Curse powers may be impressive,

261
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:20,525
but the consequences
of using them are dire.

262
00:14:20,608 --> 00:14:22,233
You must trust me.

263
00:14:22,317 --> 00:14:24,983
Don't worry about it.
I've got it under control.

264
00:14:25,067 --> 00:14:27,442
[FITORIA] That won't be
the case for much longer.

265
00:14:27,525 --> 00:14:28,983
[NAOFUMI]
I appreciate the concern,

266
00:14:29,067 --> 00:14:32,608
but I need dragon material and
the Rage Shield to survive.

267
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:36,483
Fine. Do what you must.

268
00:14:41,692 --> 00:14:43,858
I got what I needed.

269
00:14:43,942 --> 00:14:45,525
[FITORIA]
Are you quite finished?

270
00:14:45,608 --> 00:14:47,942
Yeah, but... what about...

271
00:14:48,025 --> 00:14:51,108
[FITORIA] I'll have my family
bring the remains along with us.

272
00:14:51,192 --> 00:14:52,942
[NAOFUMI]
All right.

273
00:14:53,025 --> 00:14:54,525
Get in the wagon, please.

274
00:14:54,608 --> 00:14:57,192
I'll have some questions
when we arrive.

275
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:00,650
[FITORIA]
Portal.

276
00:15:06,817 --> 00:15:09,025
[gasps] What just happened?

277
00:15:09,108 --> 00:15:11,608
Some kind of
instant travel magic.

278
00:15:12,650 --> 00:15:14,025
[NAOFUMI]
Look at that...

279
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:16,983
Impressive ruins.

280
00:15:17,067 --> 00:15:19,192
[RAPHTALIA]
Imagine the history behind them.

281
00:15:19,275 --> 00:15:21,025
[FILO]
What a dump!

282
00:15:21,108 --> 00:15:23,775
[FITORIA] Supposedly, these are
the remnants of the civilization

283
00:15:23,858 --> 00:15:25,942
defended by the original heroes.

284
00:15:26,025 --> 00:15:28,442
[NAOFUMI]
You don't sound too sure.

285
00:15:28,525 --> 00:15:30,900
They've been like this
since before I was born,

286
00:15:30,983 --> 00:15:33,567
but I watch over them now.

287
00:15:33,650 --> 00:15:36,275
This is a filolial
sanctuary, huh?

288
00:15:36,358 --> 00:15:37,608
[FITORIA]
Correct.

289
00:15:37,692 --> 00:15:40,150
In fact, I'm not supposed
to bring humans here.

290
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:42,275
Wow!

291
00:15:42,358 --> 00:15:45,442
[NAOFUMI] Guess that means we'll
be safe here for the time being.

292
00:15:45,525 --> 00:15:47,775
[stomach growls]

293
00:15:49,025 --> 00:15:52,567
Perhaps... you should all
rest here for a little while.

294
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:55,525
Yeah. Let's take a break.

295
00:15:55,608 --> 00:15:57,400
Yippee! [giggles]

296
00:15:57,483 --> 00:16:00,233
Well it sure has
been a long day!

297
00:16:01,275 --> 00:16:03,900
I wonder how Keel and
the other kids are doing.

298
00:16:03,983 --> 00:16:07,650
Van and the demi-humans are
with 'em. They'll be fine.

299
00:16:07,733 --> 00:16:09,650
Yeah, you're right.

300
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:11,525
[NAOFUMI] Why don't we
have something to eat?

301
00:16:11,608 --> 00:16:13,275
I bet you're all hungry.

302
00:16:23,900 --> 00:16:25,733
Time to dig in. [giggles]

303
00:16:28,483 --> 00:16:30,608
This is a little bit awkward.

304
00:16:30,692 --> 00:16:31,608
[filolials squawking]

305
00:16:31,692 --> 00:16:34,192
[RAPHTALIA]
And I feel guilty.

306
00:16:34,275 --> 00:16:35,775
Whatever works for you.

307
00:16:36,817 --> 00:16:38,233
Isn't it yummy?

308
00:16:38,317 --> 00:16:39,650
It's delicious.

309
00:16:39,733 --> 00:16:41,608
They could almost be sisters.

310
00:16:41,692 --> 00:16:44,858
I know. Both of them are
really sloppy eaters.

311
00:16:44,942 --> 00:16:47,442
Uhh, hey, Master Naofumi?

312
00:16:47,525 --> 00:16:49,108
[NAOFUMI]
Hm?

313
00:16:49,192 --> 00:16:54,108
--[filolials squawking]
--[NAOFUMI gasps, sighs]

314
00:16:54,192 --> 00:16:57,067
All right, fine!
I'll make some for you, too!

315
00:16:57,150 --> 00:17:00,317
Bring me ingredients and
the biggest pots you've got!

316
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:06,692
[NAOFUMI sighs]

317
00:17:07,817 --> 00:17:09,025
[NAOFUMI]
How the heck did I end up

318
00:17:09,108 --> 00:17:12,025
feeding an entire
Kentucky-fried farm?

319
00:17:14,067 --> 00:17:15,483
What's up?

320
00:17:15,567 --> 00:17:17,525
Don't tell me you want seconds.

321
00:17:17,608 --> 00:17:18,775
No thanks, I'm full.

322
00:17:18,858 --> 00:17:21,233
But I would like to
have our talk now.

323
00:17:27,983 --> 00:17:29,858
[FITORIA] I'd like to know
how that monster came to be

324
00:17:29,942 --> 00:17:32,275
released from its seal.

325
00:17:32,358 --> 00:17:35,817
I thought you showed up to
save us because you knew.

326
00:17:35,900 --> 00:17:37,525
[FITORIA] I was there
because I was told that

327
00:17:37,608 --> 00:17:41,233
a new candidate for the
next queen had been found.

328
00:17:41,317 --> 00:17:43,192
[NAOFUMI]
Candidate for queen...

329
00:17:43,275 --> 00:17:44,858
You mean Filo?

330
00:17:44,942 --> 00:17:45,942
[FITORIA]
Yes.

331
00:17:46,025 --> 00:17:47,817
[NAOFUMI]
Can I ask you something?

332
00:17:47,900 --> 00:17:49,192
[FITORIA]
Go ahead.

333
00:17:49,275 --> 00:17:51,483
Why is it that Filo's
growing so much differently

334
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:54,900
and so much bigger than
almost any other filolial?

335
00:17:54,983 --> 00:17:56,567
[FITORIA]
She's like me.

336
00:17:58,692 --> 00:18:00,733
[FITORIA]
A hero is raising her.

337
00:18:00,817 --> 00:18:02,858
[NAOFUMI gasps]

338
00:18:02,942 --> 00:18:04,067
[FITORIA]
Now tell me.

339
00:18:04,150 --> 00:18:07,067
Why was that monster
released from its seal?

340
00:18:07,150 --> 00:18:12,358
[MELTY, FILO snoring]

341
00:18:14,275 --> 00:18:15,567
[sighs]

342
00:18:15,650 --> 00:18:17,317
What's wrong with you?

343
00:18:17,400 --> 00:18:18,900
I am appalled.

344
00:18:18,983 --> 00:18:21,067
You Cardinal Heroes
should all be ashamed,

345
00:18:21,150 --> 00:18:24,317
squabbling with each other when
the next Wave is approaching.

346
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:26,775
Gimme a break. They started it!

347
00:18:26,858 --> 00:18:28,858
[FITORIA] The Shield Hero
has always been shunned

348
00:18:28,942 --> 00:18:31,442
by the human
supremacist countries.

349
00:18:31,525 --> 00:18:33,317
Okay, then you
should understand.

350
00:18:33,400 --> 00:18:35,608
That's the whole reason we're
trying to cross the border--

351
00:18:35,692 --> 00:18:38,150
[FITORIA]
Leaving won't solve anything.

352
00:18:38,233 --> 00:18:40,025
Work it out.

353
00:18:40,108 --> 00:18:42,733
The humans and demi-humans
may hate each other,

354
00:18:42,817 --> 00:18:45,567
but the heroes mustn't
fight amongst themselves.

355
00:18:51,775 --> 00:18:53,275
[NAOFUMI groans]

356
00:18:54,775 --> 00:18:56,692
[FITORIA] Don't you know
about the hourglass?

357
00:18:56,775 --> 00:18:59,025
All four of you
certainly should.

358
00:18:59,108 --> 00:19:01,400
If you're talking about
the dragon hourglass,

359
00:19:01,483 --> 00:19:03,150
yeah, we all know about it.

360
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:05,483
Then why aren't you fighting
the Waves of Catastrophe

361
00:19:05,567 --> 00:19:06,900
across the world?

362
00:19:06,983 --> 00:19:09,233
[NAOFUMI gasps]
Wait a second.

363
00:19:09,317 --> 00:19:11,108
Are you saying the
Waves of Catastrophe

364
00:19:11,192 --> 00:19:13,608
don't just happen
inside of Melromarc?

365
00:19:14,650 --> 00:19:16,192
No, they happen everywhere.

366
00:19:16,275 --> 00:19:18,983
The four heroes are meant
to go to one country each

367
00:19:19,067 --> 00:19:20,608
every time there's a Wave.

368
00:19:20,692 --> 00:19:23,775
But nobody ever
told me about that.

369
00:19:23,858 --> 00:19:25,858
[FITORIA] I've been traveling
the world in your stead,

370
00:19:25,942 --> 00:19:27,108
whenever I'm asked.

371
00:19:27,192 --> 00:19:29,817
But you four aren't
helping anywhere else.

372
00:19:29,900 --> 00:19:31,817
[NAOFUMI] Hell, I just
found out other countries

373
00:19:31,900 --> 00:19:34,025
had their own hourglasses.

374
00:19:34,108 --> 00:19:36,192
[FITORIA] Honestly,
what happens to the humans

375
00:19:36,275 --> 00:19:37,650
doesn't matter to me.

376
00:19:37,733 --> 00:19:39,983
I'm only fighting because
the hero who raised me

377
00:19:40,067 --> 00:19:41,817
asked me to do so.

378
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:44,400
[NAOFUMI]
He asked? Or told?

379
00:19:44,483 --> 00:19:46,108
[FITORIA]
My job is to protect the world

380
00:19:46,192 --> 00:19:48,192
and keep its people safe.

381
00:19:48,275 --> 00:19:49,733
[NAOFUMI]
She doesn't care about humans,

382
00:19:49,817 --> 00:19:51,650
but she wants to save them?

383
00:19:52,733 --> 00:19:55,025
[FITORIA] But I can't
do that all by myself.

384
00:19:55,108 --> 00:19:57,400
I need the heroes to help me.

385
00:19:57,483 --> 00:19:59,317
[NAOFUMI] Honestly,
you seem a lot more capable

386
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,692
than any of us.

387
00:20:00,775 --> 00:20:02,942
[FITORIA]
That may be true for now,

388
00:20:03,025 --> 00:20:04,817
but eventually...

389
00:20:06,442 --> 00:20:08,108
[FITORIA]
...I won't be enough.

390
00:20:10,192 --> 00:20:13,275
[NAOFUMI] So that's why you
need the heroes to help you.

391
00:20:13,358 --> 00:20:14,900
[FITORIA]
Exactly.

392
00:20:24,567 --> 00:20:26,150
[REN]
Is this the place?

393
00:20:26,233 --> 00:20:27,858
Yeah, I think so.

394
00:20:37,608 --> 00:20:38,983
[ITSUKI gasps]

395
00:20:39,067 --> 00:20:40,483
No question.

396
00:20:40,567 --> 00:20:43,067
The Three Heroes Church is
definitely hiding something.

397
00:20:43,150 --> 00:20:44,650
[REN exhales]

398
00:20:44,733 --> 00:20:47,150
[REN] Hard to believe
Naofumi was right.

399
00:20:55,817 --> 00:20:57,942
[ITSUKI]
It's some kind of archive.

400
00:20:59,483 --> 00:21:01,108
Let's take a look around.

401
00:21:07,150 --> 00:21:09,233
Mind your own business.

402
00:21:10,858 --> 00:21:13,442
[NAOFUMI] You want me to
make up with those guys?

403
00:21:13,525 --> 00:21:16,483
[FITORIA] The Cardinal Heroes
are supposed to work together.

404
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:20,275
That is absolutely crucial
to this world's protection.

405
00:21:20,358 --> 00:21:21,608
Not happening.

406
00:21:21,692 --> 00:21:23,983
The whole country,
besides those three,

407
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:25,525
wants to get rid of me.

408
00:21:25,608 --> 00:21:27,775
Don't worry, I'm aware
of what's happening.

409
00:21:27,858 --> 00:21:30,692
Regardless, the heroes must
stop fighting each other.

410
00:21:30,775 --> 00:21:33,150
You're kinda
obsessing about that.

411
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:35,858
[FITORIA] Because it is
completely unacceptable.

412
00:21:36,900 --> 00:21:38,150
Well it's a lost cause,

413
00:21:38,233 --> 00:21:41,317
'cause they don't wanna
play nice with me either.

414
00:21:41,400 --> 00:21:43,483
[FITORIA]
Are you certain?

415
00:21:43,567 --> 00:21:44,733
[NAOFUMI]
Yeah.

416
00:21:45,775 --> 00:21:46,775
I see.

417
00:21:46,858 --> 00:21:48,733
You've made up your mind then.

418
00:21:50,983 --> 00:21:54,108
[FITORIA] It's been a while,
several lifetimes, in fact.

419
00:21:54,192 --> 00:21:56,442
I can hardly remember anything.

420
00:21:56,525 --> 00:21:59,775
But I do still remember what
this means I'll have to do.

421
00:22:01,108 --> 00:22:04,067
[FITORIA] If the heroes
are fighting each other

422
00:22:04,150 --> 00:22:07,192
instead of fighting the
Waves of Catastrophe...

423
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:13,858
...then you leave me no choice.

424
00:22:13,942 --> 00:22:16,025
I must kill all four of you.

